column2: 22. How do TCP and UDP differ in the way that they establish a connection between two endpoints?

column2: 23. When OSPF learns multiple paths to a network, how does it select a route?

column5: C. It divides a reference bandwidth of 100 Mbps by the actual bandwidth of the existing interface to calculate the router with the lowest cost.
column6: D. It count the number of hops between the source router and the destination to determine the router with the lowest metric.
